y capture settings\n- support user confirmation before enabling remote exchange\n\nThe first milestone should be deliberately boring and explicit:\n\n- `crates/but-agentlog` owns agent log capture behavior\n- the GitButler CLI exposes a hidden, feature-gated `agentlog capture` command\n- the first implementation captures Codex data from an explicit transcript path\n- provenance/cursor data is written to GitMeta local storage by default\n- raw transcript records are written only with `--include-transcript`\n- no background watcher, broad machine scan, or remote exchange\n- GitMeta serialization and sync/push integration remain future work\n\nA good first command shape is:\n\n```text\nbut agentlog capture \\\n  --agent codex \\\n  --transcript-path <path> \\\n  --target project \\\n  --include-transcript\n```\n\n## Design Bias\n\nPrefer safety and auditability over clever discovery. It is better for the POC\nto capture nothing unless given an exact transcript than to accidentally capture\nthe wrong or private session.\n\n## Documents\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-07T15:37:08.721Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}